=1> Kiaran sits in the meeting room of the Grange near the fireplace sharpening and cleaning her weapons. She stares into the fire with a distant look on her face. <br>
<br>
She has brief flashes of being roughly handed to a Teir'dal female. She can vaguely remember the strange smell on the female as she is briefly brought close to her. She remembers a terrible fear, begins kicking her small feet and the scream wellowing up in her soul. The sound is never uttered as the just as soon as the fear begins so to does it end. The woman seems less threatening and smiles. &quot;She will do nicely&quot; Kiaran's feet are once again touch on the floor. <br>
<br>
<br>
She jerks up right with a shiver , and comes back to herself. She sees the fire has died. Her muscles protest as she rises and slowlys stretches working each one. Her pulse quiets and she begins to breathe easily. Shortly her small curveous body is got a soft sheen of sweat from the work out. She padds down the hall to her room and puts things away. She listens to the night sounds of the Grange with a small smile. She cleans herself up and pokes her nose to the hallway, seeing nothing she strips, climbs into bed and shortly dozes.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/udaiunusdarkenvalor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daiunus Darkenvalor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/18/02 5:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Beginging of the Lost Child</span><hr size=1> Daiunus watched the young warrioress from the shadows, wondering what inner demons Kiaran struggled with in her dreams.  After she had finished practicing and left the training hall, Daiunus emerged from the shadows, with a new enigma to solve.  &quot; So many Chosen, so many different secrets...&quot;<br>
Daiunus returned to the warroom, looking to his new mantle piece, he grinned evilly.  The war lance on the wall was old and rusty, but it held a glow that could not be denied.<br>
<br>
<br>
Daiunus Darkenvalor<br>
Thresher of the Harvest <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ulosturchin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LostUrchin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/21/02 4:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Beginging of the Lost Child</span><hr size=1> Something in the dark made Kiaran wake.  She slid from her bed naked and padded silently to the hall.  She peered into the dark of the hall, she saw nothing amiss.  She stood and listened but could not hear anything unusal in the Grange.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ulosturchin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LostUrchin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/22/02 7:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Beginging of the Lost Child</span><hr size=1> Kiaran turned and wandered back to bed when a sound stopped her.  She frowned, slid into leggings and a tunic.  There she heard it again, she followed the sound to the petitions room.  There curled up in the middle of the floor was a child.  Kia looked around and saw no one else.  &quot;What ails you child?&quot;  Two bright eyes stared at her.  &quot;I canna found my way back and I'm gonna get in trouble.&quot;  it sniffed.  Kia frowned before nodding.  &quot;You must be one of the Thresher's.&quot;  The child nodded.  &quot;Well come along then before he wakes.&quot;  Kia held out a hand.  &quot;Now mind you I am unfamiliar also so we will do this by memory, which Faeolin says a warrior I should improve.  Warriors are not made by body alone.&quot;  The pair wandered down the halls and although a few wrong turns found there way.   Kiaran watched the child settle in with the others.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ulosturchin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LostUrchin</A> at: 1/25/02 1:18:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ufaeolin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faeolin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dread Overlord</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/24/02 5:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Beginging of the Lost Child</span><hr size=1> The sound of footsteps outside her office made her start.  Knowing the hour was late, her hands slipped to the daggers sheathed below the top of her desk.  It was never safe in Neriak, not even for a Dread Overlord of the Violent Harvest.  Hearing a murmer that sounded remarkably like two children, she allowed herself to relax.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Let one of the Threshers wandering wretches misstep around me,&quot; she muttered to herself.  &quot;They will know what Hatred is.&quot;<br>
<br>
Once the words had crossed her lips, she smiled.  This was not the smile that she often carried around those who knew her best.  The drawing of her cheeks, and the baring of teeth was that of one maliciously intent upon bringing pain and suffering to others.  This was the smile of conquerors, the smile of certainty of deed.  This was a smile she had mastered well.<br>
<br>
